So, two hard working guilds expending all of their might in a combined effort to overcome an encounter that is extremely difficult to them should not feel that they have 'accomplished' anything and should suffer a shot to their 'dignity' because they had to use each other's help?<br>
<br>
Well, I'm sorry, but that is, by far, one of the most rediculous things I have ever heard before in my life.  <br>
<br>
If I need to lift a 300 pound box into the back of a truck because I want to get it to another location, but I cannot lift the 300 pounds by myself, I ask my friend to help me.  When the two of us put the box in the truck, I feel a sense of accomplishment because not only did I participate in the completion of my objective, but I also have the box in the truck now, and can benefit from that in the future.  I do not feel that I have lost any dignity or integrity because I had to ask my friend to help me.<br>
<br>
Also, now that the 300 pound box is in the truck, I don't need his help with the box any more, so there is no reason for me to make him stand around and watch me pick up smaller 50 pound boxes.<br>
<br>
You guys are grasping at straws HARD to find a reason to keep people from teaming up.  When it comes down to it, and we see that your reasons are illogical by promoting the use of reason and rules (as they currently stand), we can only conclude that the reason you want to keep people out is for those greed-based reasons that have already been stated.<br>
<br>
I personally would like to think that the larger guilds have better people than that.  But, then someone like Shogon comes along, and spews off this kind of crap.<br>
<br>
WAKE UP PEOPLE.  There is no integrity, honor, dignity, or anything else lost when people work together to accomplish a goal.  If these mobs are NOT on a rotation, and people are not breaking any of Verant's rules, then they should not feel bad about their accomplishments.  Nor should they be made to feel bad about them for no reason.<br>
