<br>
Why is teaming such a big issue?<br>
<br>
How is teaming different from a Hate raid?  (where the host guild has several other guilds with them?)<br>
<br>
I understand and agree with the reservations about teaming on Rotation mobs.<br>
<br>
What are the REAL REASONS you don't like it?<br>
Don't say its not fair to teams that don't team up, that is a Guild by Guild choice.<br>
<br>
No name calling, I am just asking for you logical reply.   You want us to back you on it, then explain it, in full, think about what you put in and maybe you won't meet the responses that you have.<br>
<br>
I see no logical reason someone (meaning guild entities) would not be allowed to team up.<br>
<br>
Most of us take part in pickup groups, that is technically teaming up to kill mobs.  I want to say more but can't think of how to say it correctly.  Besides the pure scale of the encounter, how is taking down flag mobs in teams, different than a single group hunting?  You are killing a NPC.  The only problem that most people have here is the fact that every person there does not wear the same guild tag.   What is the difference? <p>Keana Silverwolf&amp;lt;br&amp;gt;&lt;br&gt;
